parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Wheel Studs and Lug Nuts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of wheel studs and lug nuts can cause the wheel to become loose while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Lug nuts strip or break when attempting to remove the wheel
wheel studs break or become cross-threaded
lug nuts are difficult to remove
wheels are unable to be removed manually
wheels vibrate or shift while driving
lug nuts overheat and bond to the studs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting down can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down intermittently
often without warning
and may be accompanied by the check engine light coming on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine noise and vibration can be a sign of a more serious underlying problem, such as engine failure, which can lead to costly repairs and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The engine makes loud noises
such as screaming
rapping
or clicking sounds
and may be accompanied by vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption and leaks can lead to engine failure, which can cause accidents and costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine consumes excessive amounts of oil
and may be accompanied by black smoke coming from the tailpipe
and oil leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch or transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical and locking systems can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues, such as being unable to exit the vehicle.
symptoms: The electric lock system fails
causing the doors to lock or unlock unexpectedly
and may be accompanied by other electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt and engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine fails
often accompanied by loud noises
smoking
and stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors can cause the brakes to pulsate, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The brakes pulsate
the rotors are desintegrating
the brakes are worn out
the hubs are deteriorated and flaking
the disc brakes are virtually destroyed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the braking system to fail, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake lines are worn
the mechanical arm link in the wheel assembly rubs against the brake line
the brakes fail to bring the vehicle to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to accidents, loss of control, and failure to deploy airbags.
symptoms: The ABS malfunctions
the brakes lock up
the vehicle is involved in a frontal collision
the dual airbags do not deploy
extended stopping distances in snowy weather
the ABS solenoid sensor is bad
the front right brakes leak fluid
the brake pedal gets soft
vibration occurs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake calipers can cause the brakes to leak fluid, leading to a loss of braking power and accidents.
symptoms: The rear brake calipers are leaking brake fluid
the front right brakes leak fluid.
